<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1406] 2.6 is re-logging prior throwable instead of logging the throwable that is currently passed in by application code</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1406</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just want to make sure you saw the issue I submitted PR for a couple days ago.  It seems a very serious issue in 2.6:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/31&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/31&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Trask&lt;/p&gt;</description>
