                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15312991" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 20:27:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch!  This looks like a pretty simple fix and should be included in the 2.6.1 release planned for this weekend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313310" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 23:42:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; Thanks for raising this issue! &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;I believe the null check is necessary to verify that the throwable has not been set explicitly. The underlying cause is that the throwable is not always correctly cleared when the message is reused, and it&apos;s better to fix that instead.&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Scratch that, I wasn&apos;t looking at the code but speaking from memory. The proposed fix looks good. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313336" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 23:52:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would it be possible to add a unit test that fails now but passes with the fix?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15314392" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2016 16:47:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in master in commit a523dcd. Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15318039" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 7 Jun 2016 07:27:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix for this is included in the upcoming 2.6.1 release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a workaround, this issue will not occur if system property &lt;tt&gt;log4j2.enable.threadlocals&lt;/tt&gt; is set to &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; log4j is initialized.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
